| CCS-004 | Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleLibrary.bootstrap(root)` creates the six subdirectories + `index.sqlite` if missing, idempotent<br/>- documented as the canonical layout in module docstring<br/>- tests verify bootstrap on tmp dir creates all six subdirs and the SQLite file |
| CCS-005 | Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. | MUST | T1 | - `SampleSelector(library, rng_seed: int)` exposes `select(mode: ArtistMode, arc_phase: str, mood: Mapping[str,float], target_character: tuple[str,...] = (), avoid_recent: int = 5) -> SampleRecord \| None`<br/>- selection prefers samples with matching `arc_phase` and overlapping mood (dot-product over energy/valence/arousal); falls back to character_tags only; falls back to library random within source-source preference per-mode<br/>- `avoid_recent` excludes the N most-recently-played samples (per-mode rolling window)<br/>- per-mode source preference: solitary→[self,contact,room,library]; companion→[library,self,room]; working_ambience→[room,library]; evening_reflection→[self,library,theramini]; storm→[contact,library,room]<br/>- selection is deterministic given (library state, rng_seed, kwargs)<br/>- tests verify per-mode preference order, mood-overlap ranking, avoid_recent, deterministic replay |
