| CCS-015 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | MUST | T1 | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |
